## Status
The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is used by [gRPC](https://github.com/grpc) . Each `Status` message contains three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details.
You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the [API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors) .| Fields | Fields.1                                               |
|:----------|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| code  | int32 The status code, which should be an enum value of google.rpc.Code.                               |
| message | string A developer-facing error message, which should be in English. Any user-facing error message should be localized and sent in the google.rpc.Status.details field, or localized by the client. |
| details[] | Any A list of messages that carry the error details. There is a common set of message types for APIs to use.                      |
